    present and matching in kwargs. If False, keys not provided are\n    assumed to match. For example:\n    - day: friday\n    - mood: angry\n    would when passed (day='friday', _strict=False), but not\n    (day='friday', _strict=False)\n**kwargs\n    Query arguments to match against entries in the recipe\n\nReturns\n-------\nList[str]\n    A list of ingredient files from the recipe that match the query"]}, {"name": "confectioner.core.prep", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ingredients", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Given a list of ingredient files, load them as dictionaries\n\nParameters\n----------\ningredients : List[str]\n    A list of ingredient files\n\nReturns\n-------\nList[Dict[str, Any]]\n    A list of dictionaries, each one corresponding to an ingredient file"]}, {"name": "confectioner.core.mix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dish", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "ingredient", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "dicts", "type": {"name": "Literal", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Literal", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "overwrite", "xref": {"fqname": "overwrite", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "merge", "xref": {"fqname": "merge", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "lists", "type": {"name": "Literal", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Literal", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "overwrite", "xref": {"fqname": "overwrite", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "append", "xref": {"fqname": "append", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Given two ingredients (dicts), mix (recursively merge) them.\n\n# Parameters\n\ndish\n\n: The \"so-far\"; what {code}`ingredient` will be mixed into\n\ningredient\n\n: The new ingredient being added. If any entries exist in both this and\n  {code}`dish`, then the entry here is used.\n\ndicts\n\n: How to handle subdicts. When 'overwrite', a subdict from ingredient\n  will completely clobber the corresponding entry in dish. When merge,\n  the two dicts will be recursed into and merged.\n\nlists\n\n: How to handle lists. When overwrite, a list from ingredient will\n  completely clobber the corresponding entry in dish. When append, if\n  both entries are lists then the list from ingredient will be appended\n  to the list from dish\n\n# Returns\n\ndict\n\n: A new dish (dict) with the added ingredient\n"]}, {"name": "confectioner.core.bake", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "_recipe", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "_reverse", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functio